==English==

===Etymology===
Named from [[Thomas Addison]], M. D., of [[London]], who first described it.

===Noun===
#(''[[Medicine]]'') A [[morbid]] [[condition]] causing a peculiar [[brown]]ish [[discoloration]] of the [[skin]], and thought, at one time, to be due to [[disease]] of the [[suprarenal]] [[capsule]]s (two [[flat]] [[triangular]] [[body|bodies]] covering the upper part of the [[kidney]]s), but now known not to be dependent upon this causes exclusively. It is usually [[fatal]].


